  "texts": [
    "Users often exhibit temporal and context-sensitive interests when reading news.",
    "To capture such short-term dynamics, we represent a user's recent reading history as a time-ordered sequence C = {c 1, c 2,.",
    ", c k }, where each c i is an article clicked by the user.",
    "Each news article is encoded into a dense vector r i using the News Encoder described previously.",
    "While the original LSTUR utilizes GRU (Cho et al. 2014) for modeling short-term behavior, we hypothesize that LSTM can capture richer temporal dependencies-particularly when modeling longer user histories."
  ],
